Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:09.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kagami Yoshimizu Theater"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.91,0:00:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3rd year, class B...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Kuroi!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.20,0:00:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ambiguous 3cm? Does that \Nmean it's plushy? Wait!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wrapping is a uniform, \Nargh, it's not an act, pooh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.58,0:00:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta do your best, gotta just do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.29,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's time to catch 'n' release, eek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Between sweat (whoop) Sweat (whoop){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.95,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darlin', darlin', freeze! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kinda lethargic, something's kinda comin' out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I love you... Oh wait, one \Nof those was different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worrywarts, high metal bars {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.12,0:00:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tasty thoughts... And that's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.91,0:00:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heated body of that flying you-know-who{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.70,0:00:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's what you call a normal girlie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Am I the only one surprised? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seconds on pork-bone broth \Nramen with wire-hard noodles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Da da da da da {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pom-poms cheer squad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's get cherry pie {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy fun welcoming party {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look up! Sensation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Feeling of existence, \Ndot dot small planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.41,0:00:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Collided and it melted away, in total awe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go all out to sing, shi-ranger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.97,0:01:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it away! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should be the one who'll \Nbe laughing in the end{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I have the sailor suit \N← This is my conclusion{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's only Monday! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Already in a bad mood? What to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.45,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really prefer the summer outfits \N← kya! Wah! Good! (cute!) < 3{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until we approach 3 pixels, \Nno hesitations please ★{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do your best, be energetic {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My darlin', darlin' please! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.95,0:01:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kagami, do you like wafer chocolates?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.20,0:01:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like them, but why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.20,0:01:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then you can have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.29,0:01:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.80,0:01:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have some!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got more!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.54,0:01:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've still got tons more, \Nso go ahead and splurge!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, why do you have so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.52,0:01:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they come with toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.72,0:02:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't get the one I \Nwanted, so I bought a whole case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.10,0:02:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are those people \Nthat see only the toys,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.89,0:02:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are very inconsiderate to the snacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:08.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"To Each Her Own"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.11,0:02:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fox... let's see... a squirrel... a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.36,0:02:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.40,0:02:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was just wondering what would happen
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I were to associate everyone with animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.24,0:02:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I love pranks, I'd be a fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.12,0:02:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa's image is that of a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-{\i1}chan {\i0}is like a cute rodent, \Nso she'd be a squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you want to say that I'm \Nlike a tiger or a wolf, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.26,0:02:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, since you get lonely often, Kagami,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.97,0:02:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you might be a rabbit, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.63,0:02:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those twin ponytails look like ears too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.43,0:02:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a little embarrassing in \Nits own way, so knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.47,0:02:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's amusing. I wonder what \Nthe others would be like?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.47,0:02:49.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.64,0:02:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis Yui has the image of someone that \Ncheerfully runs around, so a leopard?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.61,0:02:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iwasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}is so cool and \Nawesome, so maybe a hawk?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki-{\i1}chan {\i0}has a very fluffy feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.49,0:03:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and somewhat soft, so maybe a sheep?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.62,0:03:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fumoffu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.12,0:03:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, however you look at it, Miyuki-{\i1}san {\i0}is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a cow. Especially here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.00,0:03:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're thinking like a dirty old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I read through literary magazines \Nfrom elementary school and stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at Konata's house yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Konata, you look very slovenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.81,0:03:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but surprisingly enough, you \Nkeep stuff like that properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad tells me, "Make sure \Nto keep stuff like that!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your dreams about your future \Nwere even more surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.98,0:03:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You used to have normal ideals, \Nlike vets and lawyers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.50,0:03:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's just like you, to have \Na different dream every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I look at stuff like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.83,0:03:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell what game or manga \NI was really into at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see, so that's it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.33,0:03:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It comes down to that after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.72,0:03:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though there are people \Nwho write down "a bride"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the occupation they want to be, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, that's not an occupation!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.34,0:04:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.09,0:04:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, well... I'm talking about you, Tsukasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.48,0:04:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.27,0:04:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is why airheads...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of airheads tend not \Nto realize they are, as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:15.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not an airhead!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come out and say it... \NMiyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you're like that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.15,0:04:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, without glasses, \Nwhat's your eyesight like?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worse than 20/200.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.62,0:04:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.08,0:04:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard somewhere that eating \Nblueberries is good for your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.67,0:04:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. There's also \Nbrightly-colored vegetables
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like carrots and spinach \Nthat are full of vitamin A,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and pork, sesame seeds, and liver, \Nthat are full of B vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.89,0:04:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, food with protein \Nis said to be good for the eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.64,0:04:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, LASIK treatments have become \Nrather popular nowadays...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I don't have the courage \Nto go through such an ordeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have also seen vision \Ntraining on TV and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.40,0:05:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... You sure know a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, only a little, from \Neverything that is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.08,0:05:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you know all that, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, \Nwhy isn't your vision any better?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have the knowledge, but I \Ndon't actually do those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.13,0:05:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you do them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try some of them \Nout? Like the vision training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... First, you close \Nyour eyes, then blink them open.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.31,0:05:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you keep your face still,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.02,0:05:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and move just your line of sight left \Nand right, up and down, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.61,0:05:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}! Your face! \NYour face is moving too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.78,0:05:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Oh? That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like my eyes are \Nmore tired afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.62,0:05:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think your vision \Nwill get any worse, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:06:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}, what does "{\i1}moe{\i0}" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.71,0:06:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm actually asked \Nto define it... hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.80,0:06:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely an expression of \Nemotion that you like something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I really don't know the \Ndetails about it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, you use it and you don't \Neven know what it means?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My honest opinion is that \Nif you can naturally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.10,0:06:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,accept the term as it is, you're an otaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I care, but I think \NI understand what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.46,0:06:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're focusing on doggies \Naround the world today!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.82,0:06:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daffundah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.99,0:06:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Puppies are so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, we should raise a dog too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Tsukasa. You say \Nit like it's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But can you take proper care of it, \Ntrain it, walk it, feed it, and so on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.50,0:06:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a puppy's not the same \Nthing as a grown dog, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.01,0:06:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that it's a life, \Nand not just a thing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true... I should \Nthink it over properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.25,0:06:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you've really thought about it, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:07:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's just that I'm simple-minded too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.73,0:07:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I looked up all sorts of things...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Konata.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You like this artist, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try reading it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.06,0:07:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, I get it. You're so annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.07,0:07:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in my space!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.87,0:07:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stare...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.73,0:07:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just wondering how far you've read.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did someone named Osano show up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not at that level yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.57,0:07:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, hurry up and read.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.09,0:07:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots of elections this \Nyear... It's really annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:07:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.64,0:08:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's with the \Ngloomy look on your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.12,0:08:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids facing college entrance exams \Nshould go home and promptly study...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, we were just talking about \Nhow all the elections are annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that, out of the blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.05,0:08:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how regular broadcasting \Ngets changed around
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with all the election specials, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, the other day, the first \Nepisode was delayed by four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, they show election \Nupdates in the regular broadcast too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.60,0:08:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That L-shaped frame makes \Nthe picture so tiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.44,0:08:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,election programming lets you \Nstudy about current events.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.82,0:08:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have time for all the \N"anime this, anime that" anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.32,0:08:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, election programs aren't the \Nonly thing to change broadcast times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even stuff like K-1 boots out regular \Nshows to get airtime, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.83,0:08:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi, I thought you liked martial arts?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.79,0:08:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's not something \Nthat I particularly like!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And anime shows sometimes \Nhave specials too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they don't cause trouble \Nto the programs after,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.13,0:08:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because they never run long!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:09:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, kids facing college entrance exams
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.15,0:09:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shouldn't worry about stuff \Nlike that! They need to study!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.85,0:09:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, it comes down \Nto brute force after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.69,0:09:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.36,0:09:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kona-{\i1}chan {\i0}said she didn't bring an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.15,0:09:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least watch the forecasts!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should just go home as is,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.16,0:09:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not caring whether or not I \Nget wet, like all the guys do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.84,0:09:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why don't boys care \Nwhether or not they get wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.16,0:09:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they don't have to worry \Nabout their bra showing through?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you have a point,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.67,0:09:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but don't say it out loud so frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.78,0:09:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a bit of modesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, one of you, lend me an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're going home to the same place,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.14,0:09:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and one umbrella will barely cover us both...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you leave an umbrella here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You leave your textbooks behind, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.31,0:09:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I had one until the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.65,0:09:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after using it once, I totally \Nforgot to bring another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:09:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I make a habit \Nto bring one, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:10:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you don't keep up with things, \Nyou don't learn good habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.24,0:10:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Suzume, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.21,0:10:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.58,0:10:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you're wearing a \Nraincoat and rubber boots,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you have this image that \Nit doesn't look cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right... It feels a bit childish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.63,0:10:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you see it in a \Npicture, why is it so {\i1}moe{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.35,0:10:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'd know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.31,0:10:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S'up, Konata!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.44,0:10:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning... Wait, what's wrong, Tsukasa?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.69,0:10:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got scolded because the cell phone \Nbill was really high this month!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.19,0:10:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I rarely use my cell phone, so I \Nalways pay only the basic rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.91,0:10:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it economical?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You say it's economical, but \Nif you hardly ever use it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.75,0:10:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't the basic rate you pay \Neach month be a waste of money?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.79,0:10:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not worry about the \Npetty details, Kagamin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:10:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's a text message.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.30,0:11:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please buy eggs on your way home...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will go to the store with \NSis on my way home. There.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.15,0:11:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really how you talk with your folks?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you text to each other, don't \Nyou end up speaking more politely?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I kinda see where you're coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you get used to it, \Nyour intonation changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long have you been using that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.09,0:11:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, how often do you change phones?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't two years about the right time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.17,0:11:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it around there that \Nyour battery life gives out?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.30,0:11:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure mine lasts twice... \NNo, three times as long!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.23,0:11:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm adamant about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get why you're so adamant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take good care of what I have, so \Nthings last a long time around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.11,0:11:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just leave it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.82,0:12:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are people like this out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.07,0:12:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They pay no attention to how much \Nthey spend on their hobbies,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet are really stingy \Nabout everything else...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.49,0:12:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Sis, can I borrow \Nyour world history textbook?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.66,0:12:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again? Geez, you're so helpless...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.50,0:12:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. You should be more \Ncareful next time, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.80,0:12:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'll come return it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiiragi's sister is rather clumsy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That's all the more \Nreason why I have to be reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.02,0:12:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it more like, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.81,0:12:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you have someone that you can rely on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.81,0:12:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you end up letting your guard down?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Hiiragi, you're \Nenabling her to be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really is a convincing argument...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.79,0:12:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiiragi, what time is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an alarm clock right in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:53.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shock!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legend of a violent Hiiragi \Nwhen she first wakes up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it just chipped \Nbecause I dropped it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:12:59.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"{\i1}Lagoon Engine {\i0}by Yukiru Sugisaki"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.18,0:13:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, manga is nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.05,0:13:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but read a newspaper or \Nsomething once in a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.13,0:13:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to learn about the world, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.43,0:13:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.14,0:13:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.35,0:13:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Newspapers are so difficult to read...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When there's a line break, where \Ndo you go for the next line?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought your reason \Nwas something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hey you, right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.78,0:13:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you call Miss Kobayakawa \Nout from this class?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.08,0:13:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell her Izumi, a {\i1}senior{\i0}, is here to see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.61,0:13:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobayakawa! Izumi-{\i1}sempai{\i0}, a \Nsenior, is here to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.76,0:13:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, it's so amusing how they \Nsuddenly start speaking politely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when they find out that I'm older...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:14:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I'm so jealous \Nthat you're so tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.73,0:14:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why there's so much of a difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.15,0:14:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know... But it might be \Nbecause I drink a lot of milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.36,0:14:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! I guess it's a fruit \Nof your everyday labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.03,0:14:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... It doesn't really \Ngo that easily for humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.57,0:14:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish it wasn't my height, but \Nsomewhere else, that grew...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phys Ed today is going to be \Ndodge-ball in the gymnasium,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.26,0:14:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because it's raining today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.98,0:14:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}, your image says you'd \Nbe on the court until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.18,0:14:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you look so tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also the type to last until the \Nvery end, if I'm playing infield...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.37,0:14:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's hard to aim at \Nme because I'm so small?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.64,0:14:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They both remain, but I'm sure \Nthe reasons are different...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.64,0:14:43.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really good at anything \Nthat moves my body around a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.82,0:14:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I'd feel bad if I hit Kobayakawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.82,0:14:47.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if that's so... I wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfortunate that we \Nended up on different teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.28,0:14:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're on the same team, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.43,0:14:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iwasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}seems to be \Ngood at athletic stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.50,0:15:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she looks like she'll show \Nno mercy... So she's scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.58,0:15:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Head - out of the question"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Upper body - big trouble if hit \Nhard and her condition gets worse"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.05,0:15:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lower body - big trouble \Nif she trips and gets hurt"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"But still, what would happen if \NI left it up to someone else?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked to play outfield, so it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.70,0:15:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iwasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}really is a \Ngood person after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Kobayakawa-{\i1}san{\i0}, you're on offense?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.19,0:15:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.85,0:15:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}? You're infield?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you're the catch...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean... defense...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The health rep attacked me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.99,0:15:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you're amazing, Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You precisely hit one person after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.12,0:15:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have good vision for moving \Nobjects and good athletic reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.17,0:15:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.55,0:15:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, is she mad because I'm making a fuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.22,0:15:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she's just blushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Then I guess it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.47,0:15:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really can't tell with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:15:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.93,0:16:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is what people who often \Nget misunderstood are like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you don't know that person, \Nthe impression you get changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gone anywhere on vacation \Nsince you came over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.32,0:16:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I paid homage to all the sanctuaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanctuaries?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.78,0:16:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I paid homage to the three \Ngreat sanctuaries of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.57,0:16:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, like Kamakura, Kyoto, and Nara?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.02,0:16:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Akiba in Tokyo, Nipponbashi \Nin Osaka, and Osu in Nagoya.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also going around all the notable \Nplaces in this area as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.46,0:16:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, like Tokyo Tower and Asakusa?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.84,0:16:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it. Like, Nakano and Kichijoji.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.64,0:16:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I got some dust in my eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me if you can't take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.15,0:16:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a good situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't stare at your friends \Nwith such a rotten view!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.62,0:17:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.12,0:17:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.85,0:17:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring the drinks right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so many books!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I only have stuff like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.47,0:17:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiyorin, you had times like this as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please kill me now. Just \Nkill me off in one blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.90,0:17:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.36,0:17:32.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what growth!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. She's really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.99,0:17:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, this picture looks \Na lot like Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.32,0:17:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Takarazuka!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is this me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a fable or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.37,0:17:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it's done, let me read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.88,0:17:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go drawing my friends \Nfrom such a rotten point of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}, would you \Nlike to go to Otome Road?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.18,0:18:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I plan to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.85,0:18:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otome Road? What kind of a place is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.97,0:18:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.68,0:18:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.41,0:18:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither do I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.52,0:18:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otome Road, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.40,0:18:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otome Road, or "Maiden \NRoad," is a road located
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.03,0:18:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the west of Sunshine \N60 in Ikebukuro, Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:18.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Otome Road"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots of shops that \Nspecialize in manga and anime,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as shops that are \Nfull of character goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that maniac fans gather \Nthere as much as in Akiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, unlike Akiba, there \Nare a lot of female patrons...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the street was \Nnicknamed Otome Road.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.75,0:18:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's a street \Nwhere the {\i1}fujoshi {\i0}go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Women and children"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.80,0:18:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, you write "rotten girl," \Nand read it as "{\i1}fujoshi{\i0}."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're rotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, when you put it that way, they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on, the three-second \Nrule! The three-second rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.91,0:19:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's within five seconds, the \Ngerms don't attach themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, I didn't say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.80,0:19:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The meatballs... my favorite!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.89,0:19:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the three-second rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.89,0:19:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... If you can let it slide, \Ndepending on the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.35,0:19:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.12,0:19:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning Luckies!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.78,0:19:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'd like to bring it to \Nyou with spirit again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite everything, we're already on \Nthe 18th episode of {\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yes, your navigator is a \Nfamiliar face by now, Akira Kogami!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.96,0:19:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I will do my best as Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}'s \Nassistant again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.51,0:20:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Minoru Shiraishi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, today's theme...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.89,0:20:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to introduce to you all of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the new additions to the cast... with a bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.85,0:20:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.58,0:20:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too many!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.86,0:20:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First off, we have Miss Yutaka Kobayakawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Konata's cousin who is \Nstaying with the Izumi family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.31,0:20:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her classmates, Miss Minami \NIwasaki, Miss Hiyori Tamura,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Miss Patricia Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.57,0:20:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, furthermore, we \Nhave Miss Kagami's classmates,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Misao Kusakabe, and \NMiss Ayano Minegishi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.58,0:20:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This truly is getting to be a rowdy bunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.37,0:20:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you have noticed this already,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:36.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,They're in the way, aren't they? Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.83,0:20:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but all the new members are showing \Nup in the opening sequence...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:37.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,This is in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.34,0:20:38.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It went flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.34,0:20:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how many do they have to bring \Nout before they're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.80,0:20:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already episode 18!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the status of {\i1}my {\i0}appearance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.05,0:20:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that reminds me, you had \Nan appearance, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.39,0:20:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that ultra-cute outfit, the \Nraincoat and rubber boots!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.85,0:20:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, you know what...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.69,0:20:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a chance to chat with \Nlast week's guest, Mr. Anizawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.85,0:20:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I was told that what an \Nactor needed most was flair,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.19,0:20:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a sense of presence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how you entered the \Nscene today, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.68,0:21:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only a fleeting \Nmoment, but in my eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.95,0:21:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Akira Kogami is {\i1}here{\i0}!" \Nwas written all over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.83,0:21:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.32,0:21:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.00,0:21:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, no, that's not it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, too bad! It's already \Ntime to say goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.21,0:21:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, we continue to ask for your \Nimpressions, praise, and opinions. Keep them coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.04,0:21:19.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:23.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still accepting them on \Nthe homepage, and on the radio!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, bye-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:26.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn that off!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.72,0:21:31.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,A text message?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.72,0:21:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, thanks for the hard \Nwork! Oh, no, it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that a text message?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, it wasn't! Of course \Nit wasn't anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:35.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Who were you texting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.48,0:21:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, it was from my parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.69,0:21:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.56,0:21:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um, they want me to \Ncome visit back home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.98,0:21:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you writing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.19,0:21:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.28,0:21:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.77,0:21:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I had been looking for all this time ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.53,0:21:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ For what you call the person \Nyou were destined for ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.20,0:21:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I'm sure that it is you ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.16,0:22:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Though I have no \Nbasis for saying that ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.84,0:22:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ When I see your smile ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Even ordinary everyday life ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.31,0:22:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Starts to glimmer, so \Nit's rather wondrous ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.98,0:22:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ It's like a magic spell was cast ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.77,0:22:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Feelings of affection, and \Nfeelings of loneliness ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.41,0:22:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ You taught me both of them ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.11,0:22:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ No matter how long the road ahead is ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.80,0:22:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I'm not afraid if I'm \Ntogether with you ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Such a special day as today ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.14,0:22:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I'm glad I'm spending \Nit together with you ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.26,0:22:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ With everything that I have ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.19,0:22:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I will protect everything \Nabout you forever ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.55,0:22:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I promise you ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.65,0:23:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.40,0:23:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I screwed up a bit on the falsetto.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.07,0:23:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.24,0:23:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was touched!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.15,0:23:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was touched! I was touched!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.15,0:23:10.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you! Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.70,0:23:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's such an old quote! So old!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.41,0:23:16.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.83,0:23:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's with the next \Nepisode of {\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.19,0:23:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiyori here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.87,0:23:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patricia here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.83,0:23:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patty, have you gotten used to your job yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.25,0:23:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.79,0:23:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're dealing with them, Patty,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.58,0:23:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the first-time customers \Ncan relax and enjoy their stay...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.17,0:23:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't deal with the \Nfirst-time customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.92,0:23:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.84,0:23:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only serve big spenders \Nwho come to our place often.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.43,0:23:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the store rules that we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.26,0:23:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's unexpectedly harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.43,0:23:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: There's Substance in 2-D.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.35,0:23:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.89,0:23:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
